                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 144",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 144",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 144
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Hippopotamus",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Hippo Sweat",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "A hippopotamus's sweat is an unusual reddish color that can lend them an even more frightening appearance that evokes the visage of a blood-coated monster. This sweat helps to protect the hippopotamus from becoming overheated, but it also bolsters their resistance to all manner of diseases.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 144",
                                "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 144",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                            },
                            "page": 144
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "Hippopotamuses, or hippos for short, are semiaquatic animals that spend most of their time in rivers and lakes, but they also can thrive on land.",
